# repo_map_kit: code-only, privacy-first scan scope (reference / fallback).
#
# setup.sh generates a tailored version of this by auto-detecting your source
# dirs. This file is the hand-editable fallback. Strategy: ignore EVERYTHING,
# then re-include only the source directories you opt in — so nothing is indexed
# (and nothing is sent anywhere) unless you allow it here.

# 1) Ignore everything by default
*

# 2) Re-include your source directories (edit to match your repo)
!src/
!src/**
!lib/
!lib/**
!app/
!app/**
!notebooks/
!notebooks/**

# 3) Belt-and-suspenders: never index secrets or client/private data,
#    even if they live inside an allowed dir above.
data/
**/data/
.env*
**/secrets/**
**/*secret*
**/*.key
**/*.pem

# 4) notebook-shadow sidecar (regenerable data, not code) — only relevant if you
#    use the notebook-shadow module.
notebooks/.graphify_shadow/manifest.json
